cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.CL. 

This paper deals with machine learning algorithms and their optimization with respect to a budget constraint. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with decision-making processes, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of feature labels and the focus on classification tasks suggest that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
